{"TopicId":174753,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"How detailed is the simulation of relay satellites out of physics range of the vessel with focus?","CreatedByName":"TheBeardyMan","CreatedById":25616,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-08T18:40:32Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"TheBeardyMan","CreatedById":25616,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-08T18:40:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf a relay satellite is not within physics range of the vessel with focus, what aspects of the satellite\u0027s situation affect its ability to function as a relay? For example:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nDoes the relay antenna consume power?\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nDo the solar panels produce power?\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nIs there a risk of power loss if the satellite\u0027s orientation makes it impossible to aim a solar panel at Kerbol?\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nIs there a risk of power loss if the satellite is eclipsed?\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-05-08T18:41:14Z\u0022 title=\u002205/08/2018 06:41  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMay 8, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by TheBeardyMan\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Capt. Hunt","CreatedById":97860,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-08T18:46:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nas near as I can figure, the only thing that is factored in is whether or not other vessels have line of sight on the relay.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-08T20:33:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, electrical generation/usage is not currently modeled for \u0022on rails\u0022 craft in stock KSP.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt checks signal strength. It checks if your relay is \u0022dead\u0022 -- that is, it completely ran out of EC the last time the relay had focus. Other than that, the only thing acting on the relay is gravity.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Corona688","CreatedById":2511,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-09T16:11:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223374158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174753\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221525811639\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154251\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022bewing\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n19 hours ago, bewing said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, electrical generation/usage is not currently modeled for \u0022on rails\u0022 craft in stock KSP.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReally?\u00A0 What causes probes to die when abandoned in the void?\u00A0 And what about mining?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Snark","CreatedById":125662,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-09T16:21:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223374709\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174753\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221525882278\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00222511\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Corona688\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, Corona688 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat causes probes to die when abandoned in the void?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey don\u0027t.\u00A0 Or, at least, they never have, for me.\u00A0 Unless I\u0027m misunderstanding the situation you\u0027re referring to-- do you have specific repro steps?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223374709\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174753\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221525882278\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00222511\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Corona688\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, Corona688 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd what about mining?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMining has some special code added to allow it to proceed when on rails-- therefore not relevant to this question.\u00A0 Relay satellites have nothing to do with this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe answer to the \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E\u0027s four questions,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223374057\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174753\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221525804832\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002225616\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TheBeardyMan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 hours ago, TheBeardyMan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nDoes the relay antenna consume power?\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nDo the solar panels produce power?\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nIs there a risk of power loss if the satellite\u0027s orientation makes it impossible to aim a solar panel at Kerbol?\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nIs there a risk of power loss if the satellite is eclipsed?\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...is \u0022no,\u0022 \u0022no,\u0022 \u0022no,\u0022 and \u0022no,\u0022 respectively.\u00A0 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"CrashyMcCrashFace","CreatedById":187039,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-09T17:40:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223374709\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174753\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221525882278\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00222511\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Corona688\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Corona688 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReally?\u00A0 What causes probes to die when abandoned in the void?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBeing at that perfect corner-case angle where the probe body blocks the solar panel(s).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Corona688","CreatedById":2511,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-09T18:52:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223374769\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174753\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221525887608\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022187039\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022CrashyMcCrashFace\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, CrashyMcCrashFace said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBeing at that perfect corner-case angle where the probe body blocks the solar panel(s).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, but why, if they\u0027re consuming no electricity?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rocket In My Pocket","CreatedById":154640,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-09T19:10:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf your probes are going \u0022dead\u0022 while not being controlled you must have the persistent E/C usage mod installed. (Forget the name.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs stated above, if it has power when you leave it, it\u0027ll have power forever; assuming you never come back to it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually, if you think about it; a relay doesn\u0027t even need solar panels, just batteries. Theoretically once it\u0027s up and in place, you shouldn\u0027t have any reason to ever take control of it again, and it can run off the \u0022paused\u0022 amount of juice it has forever.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-05-09T19:10:37Z\u0022 title=\u002205/09/2018 07:10  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMay 9, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Rocket In My Pocket\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"CrashyMcCrashFace","CreatedById":187039,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-09T19:19:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223374814\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174753\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221525891978\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00222511\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Corona688\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n35 minutes ago, Corona688 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, but why, if they\u0027re consuming no electricity?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe antenna might not be but the probe core is using electricity. Even in hibernate mode it seems to use a very tiny amount.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-05-09T19:28:40Z\u0022 title=\u002205/09/2018 07:28  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMay 9, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by CrashyMcCrashFace\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}